summary:
The Security Council:

Recalling previous resolutions on Côte d'Ivoire and the subregion, 
Recalling inter-mission cooperation arrangements,

1. Extends the mandate of UNOCI until 31 July 2011;
2. Requests the Secretary-General to submit a final report on UNOCI's mandate, including findings and recommendations, by 30 June 2011;
3. Authorizes the Secretary-General to extend the temporary redeployment of three infantry companies, one aviation unit, and crews from UNMIL to UNOCI until 30 June 2011;
4. Requests support from troop- and police-contributing countries;
5. Requests the Secretary-General to keep it informed of developments, measures taken, and efforts made in coordinating UNOCI and UNMIL to assist Côte d'Ivoire and Liberia in monitoring their border and surrounding areas;
6. Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
